MetLife Institutes One-Year Director Terms, Starting in 2012

-- B y   A n d r e w   F r y e
-- 
2011-06-23T20:20:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/metlife-institutes-one-year-director-terms-starting-in-2012.html
MetLife Inc. (MET) , the biggest U.S. life
insurer, said that directors appointed to the board will have
one-year terms, starting next year.  The phase-in of the new policy will be complete in 2014,
the New York-based firm said today in a regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Frye in New York at 
 afrye@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  